description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for two permanent Section Lead (band 8A) for the All Wales Genetic Laboratory, based in the Institute of Medical Genetics. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post-holder will be the Lead for one of the Clinical sections in the Genetics Laboratory and will have responsibility for the workload and activity of staff within the section. Positions are available within both the Cancer and the Constitutional Sections. The post-holder will be an authorising member of the senior Genetics Laboratory team, and will lead research and service development within the assigned section of the Genetics Laboratory. They will work closely with the team of Clinical Scientists, Technologists, Researchers and Clinicians. A registered Clinical Scientist is required for appointment to band 8A.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team at the All Wales Medical Genomics Service are dedicated to providing excellent patient care, and the post-holder will be working with the team who this year have launched the WINGS service for acutely unwell; the DPYD screening service for cancer patients in Wales and the NTRK gene fusion service for patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are searching for someone who shares our values that:&lt;br /&gt;• We care about the people we serve and the people we work with&lt;br /&gt;• We trust one another&lt;br /&gt;• We respect each other&lt;br /&gt;• We take personal responsibility&lt;br /&gt;• We treat people with kindness&lt;br /&gt;• We act with integrity&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Post holders will be expected at all times to behave in accordance with our values demonstrating commitment to the delivery of high quality services to patients.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The University Hospital of Wales is the largest hospital in Wales, on the same site as the University Of Wales College Of Medicine. It is well provided with academic and social facilities. Cardiff city centre, with its many amenities, is easily accessible.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Closing Date: 12th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sian Morgan - &lt;strong&gt;Head of Lab&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;sian.morgan22@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
